Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the concepts of communities and roles in network analysis, which are fundamental concepts in social and information networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for learning representations (node/edge embeddings) from graphs that preserve the notion of roles. 
3. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper may be relevant to software engineering as it discusses the development of new and better methods for community or role-based embeddings. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may be relevant to systems and control as it discusses the analysis and optimization of network embeddings. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may be relevant to data structures and algorithms as it discusses the mechanisms (e.g., random walks, feature diffusion) that give rise to community or role-based embeddings.
